I identified a deterministic gap worth tightening: priority policy pairs are defined, but target iteration in the compiler is not explicitly priority-ordered. I’m patching registry/compiler so high-priority cross-family pairs are evaluated first in a stable directional order, then I’ll validate with focused tests.
